0.1 Overview

What is LISA clustering?

0.2 Quick start

0.2.1 Generate toy data

set.seed(51773)
x <- round(c(runif(200),runif(200)+1,runif(200)+2,runif(200)+3,
           runif(200)+3,runif(200)+2,runif(200)+1,runif(200)),4)
y <- round(c(runif(200),runif(200)+1,runif(200)+2,runif(200)+3,
             runif(200),runif(200)+1,runif(200)+2,runif(200)+3),4)

cells <- data.frame(x,y,cellType = factor(paste('c',rep(rep(c(1:2),rep(200,2)),4),sep = '')), imageID = rep(c('s1', 's2'),c(800,800)))

ggplot(cells, aes(x,y, colour = cellType)) + geom_point() + facet_wrap(~imageID)

0.2.2 Create SegmentedCellExperiment object

cellExp <- SegmentedCellExperiment(cells, cellTypeString = 'cellType')
## There is no cellID. I'll create these 
## There is no image specific imageCellID. I'll create these

0.2.3 Generate LISA curves

LCurves <- lisa(cellExp, Rs = c(0.01,0.1, 0.5, 1))

0.2.4 Perform some clustering

kM <- kmeans(LCurves,2)
region(cellExp) <- paste('region',kM$cluster,sep = '_')

0.2.5 Plot identified regions

hatchingPlot(cellExp)
## Warning: 2 points were rejected as lying outside the specified window

hatchingPlot(cellExp, image = c('s1','s2'))
## Warning: 2 points were rejected as lying outside the specified window
## Warning: 4 points were rejected as lying outside the specified window

0.2.6 Alternatively,

df <- region(cellExp, image = 's1', annot = TRUE)


p <- ggplot(df, aes(x = x,y = y, colour = cellType)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  geom_hatching(aes(region = region) ,show.legend = TRUE, window = "concave", line.spacing = 21, nbp = 250, window.length = 0) + 
  theme_minimal() + 
  scale_region()

p
## Warning: 1 point was rejected as lying outside the specified window

  geom_point() + 
  facet_wrap(~imageID) + 
  geom_hatching(aes(region = region),show.legend = TRUE, window = "concave", line.spacing = 21, nbp = 250, window.length = 0) +

0.2.7 We can also control the hatching

p <- ggplot(df,aes(x = x,y = y, colour = cellType, region = region)) + 
  geom_point() + 
  facet_wrap(~imageID) +
  geom_hatching(window = "concave", line.spacing = 11, nbp = 1000, line.width = 1.5) +
  theme_minimal()+ 
  scale_region_manual(values = 6:7, labels = c('ab','cd'))

p
## Warning: 1 point was rejected as lying outside the specified window
